libspotify (0.0.6-3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add 'create-empty-orig' to debian/source/options instead of documenting it
    in debian/README.source.
  * Remove redundant files: debian/libspotify6.{postinst,postrm,dirs},
    debian/libspotify-dev.dirs.

 -- Stein Magnus Jodal <stein.magnus@jodal.no>  Fri, 14 Jan 2011 11:19:34 +0100

libspotify (0.0.6-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Install ChangeLog as changelog.gz. Fixes
    wrong-name-for-upstream-changelog Lintian warning.
  * Do not install LICENSE into docs. Fixes extra-license-file Lintian
    warning.
  * Make postinst/postrm specific to libspotify6. Fixes
    postinst-has-useless-call-to-ldconfig and
    postrm-has-useless-call-to-ldconfig Lintian warnings for libspotify-dev.
  * Patch manpages to fix manpage-has-bad-whatis-entry Lintian warnings.
  * Rename debian/docs and debian/manpages to debian/libspotify-dev.docs and
    debian/libspotify-dev.manpages, as they are only used by the -dev package
    anyway.
  * Build-Depends on quilt. Fixes missing-build-dependency Lintian error.
  * Increase standards version to 3.9.1. Fixes out-of-date-standards-version
    Lintian warning.
  * Add ${misc:Depends} to libspotify-dev. Fixes debhelper-but-no-misc-depends
    Lintian warning.

 -- Stein Magnus Jodal <stein.magnus@jodal.no>  Fri, 07 Jan 2011 16:02:40 +0100

